    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Traditional Japanese alloy of copper and gold. It is often subjected to a chemical process that produces a blue-black patina. Shakudo has historically been used for ornamental fittings as on katana.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
